subject: Remove mount utils
commitMessage:
Remove mount utils

Mount utils will now be provided by util-linux

Change-Id: Id77bbdb4b2aad629fd92a527d0b15f3175f11f5a
Signed-off-by: Maciej Wereski <m.wereski@partner.samsung.com>

comments.message: Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 1:

Does this change have implications for Tizen profiles that do not use busybox?

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Ryan, I think your question would rather be: does it have impaction to profile that _use_ busybox/mount :)

For the profile that do not use busybox, it will have no impact, as far as I can tell, since it is using the mount from util-linux(?), nothing changed.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

OK, Just realized mount/umount are already provided by util-linux in tizen 2.2.

There was a local systemd patch for busybox mount, so I it's obsolete now?
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1
